Name: Alear
Description: Successor to the Divine Dragon, awoken from a long sleep. Summons Emblems to lead the world to peace.

Name: Vander
Description: A Steward of the Dragon, long in the service of the Divine Dragon. He is a straight-laced, rigid gentleman.

Name: Clanne
Description: An apprentice Steward of the Dragon and the gentle twin brother of Framme.

Name: Framme
Description: An apprentice Steward of the Dragon and the determined, buoyant twin sister of Clanne.

Name: Alfred
Description: The staunch and loyal crown prince of Firene. He trains constantly to strengthen his constitution.

Name: Etie
Description: Prince Alfred's retainer. A haughty woman with a love for building muscle.

Name: Boucheron
Description: Prince Alfred's retainer. A tender- hearted man whose powerful build comes naturally.

Name: Céline
Description: The princess of Firene. Despite her gentle demeanor, she has an iron will when her people must be protected.

Name: Chloé
Description: Princess Céline's retainer. A woman of noble birth who loves fairy tales and sampling folk food.

Name: Louis
Description: Princess Céline's retainer. A smiling, refined gentleman who loves tea.

Name: Yunaka
Description: A thief encountered in a mountain settlement. She keeps a tight lid on the details of her past.

Name: Alcryst
Description: The self-torturing, wildly imaginative prince of Brodia. Has hidden talents even he isn't aware of.

Name: Citrinne
Description: Prince Alcryst's retainer. Despite her fierce demeanor, she's a noble who cares deeply for her friends.

Name: Lapis
Description: Prince Alcryst's retainer. Her quiet modesty belies her superhuman strength.

Name: Diamant
Description: The majestic crown prince of Brodia. His people trust him greatly for his strong, genuine demeanor.

Name: Amber
Description: Prince Diamant's retainer. Has a boundless enthusiasm for legends and adventure.

Name: Jade
Description: Prince Diamant's retainer. A warrior of few words who always keeps her wits about her.

Name: Ivy
Description: The mysterious, melancholy crown princess of Elusia. She never relaxes her icy royal decorum.

Name: Kagetsu
Description: Princess Ivy's retainer. A handsome young man from outside Elusia who speaks freely and without inhibition.

Name: Zelkov
Description: Princess Ivy's retainer. An enigmatic man who's always absorbed in intrigues of his own making.

Name: Fogado
Description: A freewheeling, optimistic young Sentinel. He's easygoing, but there's something mysterious about him.

Name: Pandreo
Description: A member of the Sentinels. Though deeply religious, he loves to party more than just about anyone.

Name: Bunet
Description: A member of the Sentinels, and a chef with incredibly refined senses of taste and smell.

Name: Timerra
Description: The bubbly and outgoing crown princess of Solm. Known for being accessible and approachable by all.

Name: Panette
Description: Princess Timerra's retainer. She has a tendency to speak in erratic and somewhat stilted tones.

Name: Merrin
Description: Princess Timerra's retainer. She's a dashing woman with a fondness for animals.

Name: Hortensia
Description: A mischievous, spoiled princess of Elusia. She is nonetheless devoted to her family and friends.

Name: Seadall
Description: A famous dancer of Solm. He is also a skilled fortune-teller and cultivates an aura of mystery.

Name: Rosado
Description: Princess Hortensia's retainer. He loves cute things and always maintains a bright, positive attitude.

Name: Goldmary
Description: Princess Hortensia's retainer. She seems demure on the surface, but is conceited to the core.

Name: Lindon
Description: A scholar from Elusia. Has a great hunger for knowledge, which he feeds with studies and experiments.

Name: Saphir
Description: A warrior from Brodia. She is a dauntless and determined seeker of truth.

Name: Lumera
Description: The Divine Dragon and ruler of the holy land of Lythos. Vanquished the Fell Dragon 1,000 years ago.

Name: Sombron
Description: The Fell Dragon King. A wicked creature who wields immense dark power.

Name: Éve
Description: The kind queen of Firene. A gentle soul who wishes for a world without strife or conflict.

Name: Morion
Description: The brave king of Brodia. A powerful and proud warrior, he prizes honor on the battlefield.

Name: Hyacinth
Description: The cunning king of Elusia. Worships the Fell Dragon and schemes for the advancement of his country.

Name: Seforia
Description: The free-spirited queen of Solm. Leads her country by example with heroic acts.

Name: White Hop Rabbit
Description: Long-eared rabbits that can be found hopping enthusiastically all over Elyos. Surprisingly, not all are white.

Name: Hop Rabbit
Description: Long-eared rabbits that can be found hopping enthusiastically all over Elyos. Some varieties have white fur.

Name: Eastern Freecat
Description: This breed originated in eastern Elyos. Its appearance and behavior have adapted to its surroundings.

Name: Western Freecat
Description: This breed originated in western Elyos. Its appearance and behavior have adapted to its surroundings.

Name: Southern Freecat
Description: This breed originated in southern Elyos. Its appearance and behavior have adapted to its surroundings.

Name: Northern Freecat
Description: This breed originated in northern Elyos. Its appearance and behavior have adapted to its surroundings.

Name: Firenese Cat
Description: A cat found only in Firene. This region is known for cats with black- and-white coats.

Name: Brodian Cat
Description: A cat found only in Brodia. This region is known for cats with a mix of black and brown fur.

Name: Elusian Cat
Description: A cat found only in Elusia. This region is known for cats with black markings.

Name: Solmic Cat
Description: A cat found only in Solm. This region is known for cats with a leopard-like coat.

Name: Calisson Chicken
Description: A chicken found mainly in Firene. Despite their round shape, they can fly and sometimes carry messages.

Name: Aura Eagle
Description: An eagle found mainly in Brodia. Their mastery of air currents makes them adept at long-distance flight.

Name: Iris Owl
Description: An owl found mainly in Elusia. They are strong and swift fliers, kept warm by their large feathers.

Name: Panna Camel
Description: A camel found mainly in Solm. Most Solmic households have at least one for transportation and carrying cargo.

Name: Elyosian Pigeon
Description: A wild bird found in all regions of Elyos. At times they appear in large flocks, causing a spectacle.

Name: Elyosian Seagull
Description: A wild bird that inhabits coastlines all over Elyos. They constantly try to sneak fish from the day's catch.

Name: Elyosian Dog
Description: A dog found in all regions of Elyos. These friendly, intelligent animals are often kept indoors as pets.

Name: Black Elyosian Dog
Description: A dog found in all regions of Elyos. Known for their black coats, they are friendly and easily trained.

Name: White Elyosian Dog
Description: A dog found in all regions of Elyos. Known for their white coats, they are friendly and easily trained.

Name: MÃ¨re Donkey
Description: A rare animal found only in Firene. They prefer clean water and fresh produce. Legend says they are lucky.

Name: Rutile Marmot
Description: A rare animal found only in Brodia. Considered a local guardian, they like uninhabited areas such as cliff tops.

Name: Vervain Deer
Description: A rare animal found only in Elusia. Often found deep in the forest, their shed antlers make a wondrous cure.

Name: Tartu Flamingo
Description: A rare animal found only in Solm. Royalty use these oasis-dwelling birds to send special messages.
